      <div class="subfield"><strong>$2 - Code source</strong> <div class="description">MARC code for the source of the geographic classification. Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/sourcelist/classification.html">Classification Scheme Source Codes</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> 
        <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
        </div>
   </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>INPUT CONVENTIONS</h3>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Punctuation</strong> - Period that usually precedes a Cutter number is omitted in subfield $b. Field
                     052 does not end with a period.
      </div>
      <div class="description2"><strong>Capitalization</strong> - Alphabetic characters are recorded in uppercase.
      </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>CONTENT DESIGNATOR HISTORY</h3>
      <div class="font_small"><em>Indicator 1 - Code source [NEW, 2000]</em><br>Records created prior to 2000 may contain a code # meaning <em>undefined.</em><em><br>
      0 - U.S. Dept. of Defense Classification [OBSOLETE, 2002]</em><br>
      First indicator value 0 (U.S. Dept. of Defense Classification) was made obsolete.
                        Value 1 was defined as U.S. Dept. of Defense Classification to replace it.<br>
                        <br><em>$c - Subject (MP) [OBSOLETE]</em><br>Subfield $c was made obsolete in the maps specifications in 1980. Subject
                        content descriptors are contained in the 6XX fields.
      </div>
